The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the Federalist Society's annual conference in Philadelphia. He expressed gratitude for the society's support and highlighted the importance of the Constitution and the rule of law. Pence introduced Judge Neil Gorsuch as President Trump's nominee for the Supreme Court, emphasizing his qualifications and commitment to the Constitution. Pence also addressed the opposition to Gorsuch's nomination and vowed to ensure that he receives an up or down vote in the Senate. He concluded by expressing confidence in the future of America and the ideals enshrined in its founding documents.